ple from Dover, Delaware]]\n[[Category:People from Hampshire County, West Virginia]]\n[[Category:People from New Castle County, Delaware]]\n[[Category:People from Rockingham County, Virginia]]\n[[Category:People from Salem, West Virginia]]\n[[Category:People from Washington Court House, Ohio]]\n[[Category:Salem University faculty]]\n[[Category:Wilmington College (Ohio) alumni]]\n", "name_user": "West Virginian", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eLecturer and writer:Reorganizing this section per GAR", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthur_R._M._Spaid"}
{"title_page": "Dhikr", "text_new": "{{short description|Repetition of short phrases or prayers in Islam}}\n{{for|the Quranic software|Zekr (software)}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2015}}\n{{Islam}}\n'''Dhikr''' ({{lang-ar|\u0630\u0650\u0643\u0652\u0631|\u1e0fikr}}, {{IPA-ar|\u00f0\u026akr|IPA}}), also spelled '''Zikr''', '''Thikr''' or '''Zekr''',<ref name=\"Modarresi\">{{cite book|author=Mohammad Taqi al-Modarresi|authorlink=Mohammad Taqi al-Modarresi|title=The Laws of Islam|date=26 March 2016|publisher=Enlight Press|isbn=978-0994240989|url=http://almodarresi.com/en/books/pdf/TheLawsofIslam.pdf|accessdate=22 December 2017|ref=Modarresi|language=English}}</ref>{{rp|470}} literally means \"remembrance\" or \"reminder\" and \nare devotional acts, in which phrases or prayers are repeated. It can be counted on a set of [[prayer beads]] (''[[Misbaha]]'' {{lang|ar|\u0645\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0628\u064e\u062d\u064e\u0629}}) or through the fingers of the hand. It plays a central role in [[Sufi Islam]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Le Gall |first1=Dina |title=A Culture of Sufism: Naqshbandis in the Ottoman World, 1450-1700 |date=2005 |publisher=SUNY Press |page=117 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yv-KrpzZYiYC&pg=PA117 |accessdate=22 July 2019}}</ref> A person who recites the Dhikr is called a ''\u1e0f\u0101kir'' ({{lang|ar|\u0630\u064e\u0627\u0643\u0650\u0631}}, {{IPA-ar|\u00f0a\u02d0k\u026ar|}}).\n''[[Tasbih]]'' ({{lang|ar|\u062a\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0628\u0650\u064a\u062d}}), literally meaning \"glorification\" (i.e. the saying of \"sub\u1e25\u0101na -ll\u0101h{{smallsup|i}}\" [{{lang-ar|\u0633\u064f\u0628\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650|link=no}}]) is a form of dhikr that involves the repetitive utterances of short sentences glorifying God.\nThe content of the prayers includes the [[names of God in Islam|names of God]], or a ''[[dua]]'' (prayer of supplication) taken from the [[hadith]]s or the [[Quran]].\n\n[[File:Isma allah zat-new.png|thumb|right|Allah as having been written on the disciple's heart according to Sarwari Qadri Order]]\n\n== Importance ==\nThere are several verses in the Quran that emphasize the importance of remembering the will of God by saying phrases such as \"God willing\" \"God knows best,\" and \"If it is your will.' This is the basis for dhikr. [[Al-Kahf|Surah al-Kahf]] (18), [[Ayah]] 24 states a person who forgets to say, \"God willing\", should immediately remember God by saying, \"Maybe my Lord will guide me to [something] more akin to rectitude than this.\"<ref>{{Cite quran|18|24|s=ns}}</ref> Other verses include [[Al-Ahzab|Surah al-Ahzab]] (33), Ayah 41, \"O you who have faith! Remember Allah with frequent remembrance\",<ref>{{Cite quran|33|41|s=ns}}</ref> and [[Ar-Ra'd|Surah ar-Ra'd]] (13), Ayah 28, \"those who have faith, and whose hearts find rest in the remembrance of Allah.' Look! The hearts find rest in Allah's remembrance!\"<ref name=\"quran1328\">{{Cite quran|13|28|s=ns}}</ref> Muhammad said, 'The best [dhikr] is ''l\u0101 \u02beil\u0101ha \u02beill\u0101 -ll\u0101h{{smallsup|u}}'' (\"There is no deity but God\"), and the best supplicatory prayer is ''\u02beal\u1e25amdu lill\u0101h{{smallsup|i}}'' (\"All praise is due to God\").<ref>Razi, Najm al-Din. The Path of God\u2019s Bondsman: From Origin to Return. Trans. Hamid Algar. North Haledon, New Jersey: Islamic Publications International, 1980. Print.</ref>\n\n[[Muslim|Muslims]] believe dhikr is one of the best ways to enter the higher level of [[Jannah|Heaven]] and to glorify the [[Tawhid|Monotheistic Oneness]] of [[Allah|God]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Dhikr, remembrance of God|url = http://sunnah.org/ibadaat/dhikr.htm|website = sunnah.org|accessdate = 2015-09-28}}</ref>\n\nTo Sufis, dhikr is seen as a way to gain spiritual enlightenment and achieve union (''visal'') or annihilation (''fana'') in God. All Muslim sects endorse individual rosaries as a method of meditation, the goal of which is to obtain a feeling of peace, separation from worldly values ([[dunya]]), and, in general, strengthen [[Iman (concept)|Iman]] (faith).{{cn|date=January 2015}}\n\n== Common Types of Dhikr ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\n|-\n! style=\"width:33%;\"| Arabic <hr> Qur\u02beanic Spelling || style=\"width:30%;\"| Transliteration <hr> [[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]] || style=\"width:33%;\"| Phrase\n|-\n|\u0628\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0645\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0670\u0646\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062d\u0650\u064a\u0645\u0650|| [[Basmala|bismi -ll\u0101hi r-ra\u1e25m\u0101ni r-ra\u1e25\u012bm{{smallsup|i}}]] <hr> /bis.mi\u203fl.la\u02d0.hi\u200c\u203fr.ra\u0127.ma\u02d0.ni \u203fr.ra.\u0127i\u02d0.mi/ || In the name of God, the All-Merciful, the Especially-Merciful.\n|-\n|\u0623\u064e\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0630\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u064e \u0671\u0644\u0634\u064e\u0651\u064a\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062c\u0650\u064a\u0645\u0650 <hr> \u0623\u064e\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0630\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u064e \u0671\u0644\u0634\u064e\u0651\u064a\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0670\u0646\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062c\u0650\u064a\u0645\u0650|| \u02bea\u02bf\u016b\u1e0fu bi-ll\u0101hi mina \u0161-\u0161ay\u1e6d\u0101ni r-raj\u012bm{{smallsup|i}} <hr> /\u0294a.\u0295u\u02d0.\u00f0u bil.la\u02d0.hi mi.na\u203f\u0283.\u0283aj.t\u02e4a\u02d0.ni\u203fr.ra.d\u0361\u0292i\u02d0.mi/ || I seek refuge in God from the pelted Satan.\n|-\n|\u0623\u064e\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0630\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0633\u064e\u0651\u0645\u0650\u064a\u0639\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0645\u0650 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u064e \u0671\u0644\u0634\u064e\u0651\u064a\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062c\u0650\u064a\u0645\u0650 <hr> \u0623\u064e\u0639\u064f\u0648\u0630\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0633\u064e\u0651\u0645\u0650\u064a\u0639\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0645\u0650 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u064e \u0671\u0644\u0634\u064e\u0651\u064a\u0652\u0637\u064e\u0670\u0646\u0650 \u0671\u0644\u0631\u064e\u0651\u062c\u0650\u064a\u0645\u0650|| \u02bea\u02bf\u016b\u1e0fu bi-ll\u0101hi s-sam\u012b\u02bfi l-\u02bfal\u012bmi mina \u0161-\u0161ay\u1e6d\u0101ni r-raj\u012bm{{smallsup|i}} <hr> /\u0294a.\u0295u\u02d0.\u00f0u bil.la\u02d0.hi\u203fs.sa.mi\u02d0.\u0295i\u203fl.\u0295a.li\u02d0.mi mi.na\u203f\u0283.\u0283aj.t\u02e4a\u02d0.ni\u203fr.ra.d\u0361\u0292i\u02d0.mi/ || I seek refuge in God, the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing, from the pelted Satan.\n|-\n|\u0633\u064f\u0628\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650 <hr> \u0633\u064f\u0628\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0670\u0646\u064e \u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650|| [[Tasbih|sub\u1e25\u0101na -ll\u0101h{{smallsup|i}}]] <hr> /sub.\u0127a\u02d0.na\u203f\u026b.\u026ba\u02d0.hi/ || Glorified is God.\n|-\n|\u0671\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0645\u0652\u062f\u064f \u0644\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u0650|| [[Alhamdulillah|\u02beal\u1e25amdu lill\u0101h{{smallsup|i}}]] <hr> /\u0294al.\u0127am.du lil.la\u02d0.hi/ || All praise is due to God.\n|-\n|\u0644\u064e\u0627 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0670\u0647\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u064f|| [[Shahada|l\u0101 \u02beil\u0101ha \u02beill\u0101 -ll\u0101h{{smallsup|u}}]] <hr> /la\u02d0 \u0294i.la\u02d0.ha \u0294il.la\u203f\u026b.\u026ba\u02d0.hu/ || There is no deity but God.\n|-\n|\u0671\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0670\u0647\u064f \u0623\u064e\u0643\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064f|| [[Takbir|\u02beall\u0101hu \u02beakbar{{smallsu